text: Alika Milova (born 5 September 2002), known mononymously as Alika, is an Estonian singer. She has participated in numerous singing TV shows, such as The Baltic Voice and Estonian Idol, which she won. In 2023, she won Estonia's national selection for the Eurovision Song Contest. This gave her the right to represent Estonia in the Eurovision Song Contest 2023 with the song "Bridges". She finished in 8th place out of 26 finalists. == Sources == Category:Estonian singers Category:2002 births Category:Living people Category:Eurovision Song Contest entrants
